Description of syntypes .
(Data from Kraepelin’s ( 1903 ) redescription in parentheses). Length 60–63 ( 70 ) mm. Antennae (long) of 17 articles, the basal 2.25–2.33 glabrous dorsally. Forcipular coxosternal teeth 4 + 4 (
Fig. 50
) or 4 + 3 . Specimen 2 has, atypically, 6 + 4 (
Fig. 51
) ( 4 + 4 large teeth).

Sternites without paramedian sutures but with three weak obscure depressions, or only one, or none (two weak lateral depressions in middle of sternite and one small median at hind margin). Sternite of ultimate leg-bearing segment ratio of length to width: 1.17 : 1 to 1.3 : 1 ( 1 ½ times as long as wide) with sides converging and posterior margin slightly concave (
Fig. 52
) or straight (
Fig. 53
) (posterior corners almost rectangular). Coxopleural process moderately long with two apical and one lateral spine. No dorsal spine.
